programme.title: Cathedrals Across America
programme.sub-title: Holy Mass at the Annual Sea Services Pilgrimage
programme.desc: Annual Pilgrimage for the Sea Services held at the Seton Shrine in Emmitsburg, Md.

programme.title: Catholics Come Home
programme.sub-title: Young Father Converts With His Family
programme.desc: After spending years as an inactive Presbyterian, Jason Staas underwent a journey to the Catholic Church with his wife and six children.

programme.title: Life on the Rock
programme.desc: Fr. Mark Mary and his co-host, Doug Barry, host a wide variety of guests, from athletes to actors and everything in between, on this dynamic Christ-centered, youth-oriented live show.

programme.title: Holy Rosary From Lourdes
programme.desc: Pilgrims from around the world gather and pray the Rosary from the Lourdes Grotto in France, site of the famous apparitions by the Blessed Virgin Mary in 1858.

programme.title: Franciscan University Presents
programme.desc: Dr. Ralph Martin discusses living in the power of the Holy Spirit, what the Holy Spirit says to todays Church, and what evangelization means in an ear of tolerance and acceptance.

programme.title: Mass For The Jubilee of The Missionary World and The Jubilee of Migrants
programme.desc: Celebrated by Pope Leo XIV from St. Peters Basilica.

programme.title: Litany of the Sacred Heart
programme.desc: The Franciscan Missionaries of the Eternal Word pray the Litany of the Sacred Heart.

programme.title: St. Francis of Assisi: Sign of Contradiction
programme.desc: A journey through the real life of one of the Catholic Churchs most beloved saints, St. Francis of Assisi, and how his struggle to find meaning and purpose lead him to encounter Jesus Christ.

programme.title: EWTN Religious Catalogue
programme.sub-title: Our Lady Of Good Remedy Outdoor Shrine
programme.desc: Celebrate your faith as EWTN Religious Catalogue presents a unique array of religious items - from books and paintings to rosaries and statues - and everything in between.

programme.title: The Faithful Traveler in Portugal
programme.desc: Diana and David von Glahn explore Portugals sacred sites. From monasteries and convents to cathedrals and shrines, follow as a faithful traveler to discover this stunning country.

programme.title: The Doctors of the Church
programme.desc: Dr Matthew Bunson talks about the life and work of St Francis de Sales, who spread the message of Gods abundant love during the Protestant Reformation and saved the Church.

programme.title: The Holy Rosary With Mother Angelica
programme.desc: Mother Angelica and the Poor Clares of Perpetual Adoration recite the Joyful Mysteries of the Rosary from the Shrine of the Most Blessed Sacrament in Hanceville, Ala.

programme.title: EWTN Bookmark
programme.desc: Anthony DeStefano introduces his Halloween-themed childrens book discussing prayer, penance and souls in purgatory.

programme.title: Grab Your Catechism with Fr. Connor
programme.desc: Fr. Connor expands upon the fifth commandment, and how it teaches that every human life is sacred from conception to natural death.

programme.title: The Quest for Shakespeare
programme.desc: Joseph Pearce delivers a scholarly exploration of the faith of William Shakespeare; he was practicing Catholic at a time of intense persecution; Joseph Pearce looks at the controversy surrounding his marriage, the baptism of his children, and more.

programme.title: Catechesis: Communion with Jesus Christ
programme.desc: An examination of the Churchs teaching on the afterlife.

programme.title: The Chaplet of St. Michael
programme.desc: Mother Angelica and the Nuns of Our Lady of the Angels Monastery ask for the intercession of the Prince of the Heavenly Hosts and the nine Choirs of Angels, as they pray the chaplet of St. Michael.

programme.title: Holy Land Rosary
programme.desc: Fr. Mitch Pacwa leads the Joyful Mysteries of the Rosary from the actual holy sites and shrines where they took place, bringing the Gospels to life and offering a deeper understanding of the Rosary meditations.

programme.title: The Litany of the Blessed Virgin Mary
programme.desc: A beautiful prayer in honor of the Blessed Virgin Mary from the Shrine of the Most Blessed Sacrament in Hanceville, Alabama.

programme.title: Daily Mass: Olam Daily Mass
programme.desc: The Franciscan Missionaries of the Eternal Word celebrate the Holy Sacrifice of the Mass from the Our Lady of Angels Chapel in Irondale, Ala.

programme.title: Living Divine Mercy
programme.sub-title: Fr. Chris Explains Our Lady of the Rosary
programme.desc: Fr. Chris explains the beautiful Catholic devotion to Our Lady of the Rosary.
